comments: Vanderbilt (UTA) is already in Branham's (SAS) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Sochan (SAS) initiates contact with Markkanen's (UTA) arm, which affects his jump shot attempt.
Beasley (UTA) steps slightly forward towards Sochan (SAS), and marginal contact occurs as Markkanen (UTA) simultaneously blocks the shot attempt.
Markkanen (UTA) legally contests Vassell's (SAS) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Collins (SAS) extends his forearm into Vanderbilt's (UTA) body and dislodges him from his rebounding position.
Poeltl (SAS) is already in Vanderbilt's (UTA) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Markkanen (UTA) legally contests Vassell's (SAS) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Markkanen (UTA) moves alongside Jones' (SAS) path and the contact during the driving shot attempt is marginal.
Jones (SAS) is bracing for the contact from Conley (UTA) and marginal contact occurs as Jones releases from the contact.
Beasley (UTA) brings his hands towards Sochan (SAS) and marginal contact occurs off ball.
Beasley (UTA) is moving alongside Jones' (SAS) path and marginal contact occurs as he defends the driving shot attempt.
Sochan (SAS) legally contests Markkanen's (UTA) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Jones (SAS) cleanly deflects the ball away from Sexton (UTA) during rebounding.
Jones (SAS) is the last player to touch the ball before the ball goes out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to Utah.
Sexton (UTA) commits a take foul on Vassell (SAS).
